putAttachmentModelValueExpression

public void putAttachmentModelValueExpression(java.lang.String key,
                                              java.lang.String elExpressionSuffix,
                                              java.lang.Class expectedType)
Create and store a ValueExpression based upon the AttachmentModel ValueExpression by suffixing the EL expression. The ValueExpression will be created like: if AttachmentModel=#{binding.Attachment1} and elExpressionSuffix=currentRow then the result will be #{binding.Attachment1.currentRow}. Note that the AttachmentModel ValueExpression must already exist or an exception will be thrown.

Parameters:
key - the key to store the new ValueExpression against.
elExpressionSuffix - the suffix to put against the AttachmentModel.
expectedType - the expected type of result of running the new expression.
